40|$|Space Innovations Limited (SIL) have {{developed}} a series of low-cost S-Band ground stations for use with low-Earth orbit satellites. The SGS- 2. 4 {{will be used for}} the ground segment being provided by SAS for ESA 2 ̆ 7 s PROBA (PRoject for On-Board Autonomy) satellite mission. It consists of a motorised 2. 4 m dish antenna, S-band feed with integral diplexer and low noise amplifier, up- and down-converters, variable data rate demodulator, <b>sub-carrier</b> <b>generator</b> and sweeper, high power amplifier (HPA) and an ESA/CCSDS packet standard packetiser/de-packetiser. Universal time is supplied via a GPS based time standard. All units are 192 ̆ 2 rack mounted and are under the control of a 2 ̆ 7 master 2 ̆ 7 PC which also controls the antenna...|$|E

